Context:
The George Brown College offers free and confidential mental health services to registered students with a valid Student ID number. The services are provided at three campuses: St. James (200 King St. East, Room 582C), Casa Loma (160 Kendal Ave., Building C, Room C317), and Waterfront (51 Dockside Dr., Room 225). Students can contact the following emails and phone numbers for each campus to access these services:

St. James: letstalk@georgebrown.ca, 416-415-5000 ext. 2107
Casa Loma: letstalkcl@georgebrown.ca, 416-415-5000 ext. 4585
Waterfront: letstalkwf@georgebrown.ca, 416-415-5000 ext. 5370

The college offers online resources and virtual appointments for counselling services. Emergency crisis resources are also available. The services are open to all registered George Brown College students.

Addresses:
St. James: 200 King St. East, Toronto ON M5A 3W8, Canada
Casa Loma: 160 Kendal Ave., Toronto ON M5R 1M3, Canada
Waterfront: 51 Dockside Dr., Toronto ON M5A 1B6, Canada
